excerpt: Museum displaying the ancient finds of the Jinsha Site, including ivory, gold & jade artifacts.
detail_description: The Jinsha Site Museum Tourist Center in Chengdu is a remarkable museum that showcases the ancient artifacts discovered at the Jinsha Site. This site, dating back to the 17th to 11th centuries BC, offers a glimpse into the Shu era with its extensive collection of gold, jade, bronze, stone, and ivory relics. The museum's five halls exhibit thousands of objects and provide insight into the historical culture of Chinese ancestors from around 2900-3200 years ago.
name: Jinsha Site Museum Tourist Center
address: 2 Jinshayizhi Rd, Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610074

excerpt: Active Buddhist monastery & temple with a serene garden, plus a teahouse serving vegetarian fare.
detail_description: Wenshu Yuan Monastery is a well-preserved Buddhist temple in Chengdu, dedicated to Manjushri Bodhisattva. The monastery features a serene garden and offers cultural activities such as free Buddhist lectures. It houses numerous Buddhist and historical relics, including bronze Buddha statues from the Ming Dynasty and wooden Buddha statues from the Qing Dynasty. Visitors can also enjoy vegetarian fare at the on-site teahouse.
name: Wenshu Yuan Monastery
address: 66 Wenshuyuan St, Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610084

excerpt: Giant Panda conservation facility allowing visitors to observe pandas & other endangered animals.
detail_description: The Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding is a renowned conservation facility that offers visitors the chance to observe giant pandas and other endangered animals. Situated about 10 kilometers from downtown Chengdu, this base covers approximately 247 acres and serves as a scientific research and breeding center, public education site, and educational tourism destination. It is dedicated to the protection and breeding of endangered Chinese wildlife such as giant pandas and red pandas. Visitors can also opt for a panda volunteering experience at the center.
name: Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding
address: 1375 Xiongmao Blvd, Chenghua District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610016

excerpt: Chengdu is the capital of southwestern China's Sichuan province. Chengdu's history dates back to at least the 4th century B.C., when it served as capital for the Shu Kingdom. Artifacts from that dynasty are the focus of the Jinsha Site Museum. The city is also home to the famous Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding, a conservation center where visitors can view endangered giant pandas in a natural habitat.
detail_description: Chengdu, the vibrant capital of Sichuan province in southwestern China, boasts a rich history that stretches back to at least the 4th century B.C. As the former capital of the Shu Kingdom, it is home to significant historical sites like the Jinsha Site Museum, which showcases artifacts from this ancient dynasty. A highlight for visitors is the Chengdu Research Base of Giant Panda Breeding, where you can observe these adorable endangered creatures in an environment that mimics their natural habitat.
name: Chengdu
address: Sichuan, China

detail_description: Du Fu Thatched Cottage, located in Chengdu, is a memorial to the renowned poet who resided there during the Tang Dynasty. After fleeing to Chengdu in 759 following the An-Shi rebellion, he penned over 240 poems that are now treasured national works. The site offers insight into his life and work. In addition to this historical gem, visitors can explore other attractions such as Kuanzhai Alley and Jinsha Site Museum within Chengdu city.
name: Du Fu Thatched Cottage （Southwest Gate）
address: M25G+QJV, Caotang Rd, 青羊宫商圈 Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610074

excerpt: Popular urban green space featuring a pond, a waterside cafe, 2 museums & verdant, shaded pathways.
detail_description: People's Park, also known as Renmin Park, is a beloved urban oasis in the heart of Chengdu. This more than 100-year-old park offers a serene escape with its picturesque pond, shaded pathways, and vibrant greenery. Visitors can enjoy a leisurely stroll or relax at the waterside cafe while taking in the tranquil surroundings.
name: People's Park
address: 9 Citang St, Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610015

excerpt: Spacious museum of Sichuan cuisine & culture, featuring exhibits, cooking classes & more.
detail_description: The Sichuan Cuisine Museum of Chengdu is a unique and spacious museum that showcases the rich culture and culinary traditions of Sichuan. Visitors can explore exhibits featuring antiques, relics, and kitchen utensils related to Sichuan cuisine. The museum offers cooking classes where guests can learn to prepare authentic Sichuan dishes under the guidance of a qualified chef.
name: Sichuan Cuisine Museum of Chengdu
address: China, 四川省成都市郫县古城镇荣华北巷8号

detail_description: Located near Tianfu Square, Chengdu Museum is the city's largest comprehensive museum, covering 12,000 square meters and boasting a total building area of 65,000 square meters. The museum consists of themed exhibition halls showcasing the history and culture of Chengdu as well as temporary exhibition spaces. With its distinctive exterior covered in brass plates, the museum offers free entrance to visitors except on Mondays.
name: Chengdu Museum
address: 18 十二桥路, Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610032

detail_description: Kuanzhai Alley Waiwei Parking Lot Er, also known as Wide and Narrow Alley or Kuanzhai Ancient Street of Qing Dynasty, is a historic area in Chengdu that comprises three parallel alleys from the Qing dynasty. Visitors can immerse themselves in the local Chengdu life while exploring ancient-style buildings, sampling delicious Sichuan snacks, and admiring exquisite Sichuan handicrafts.
name: Kuanzhai Alley Waiwei Parking Lot Er
address: M382+HHQ, Xiatongren Rd, Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610032

excerpt: Large museum showcasing ancient pottery, Buddhist art & changing international exhibits.
detail_description: Sichuan Museum, located near Tianfu Square in Chengdu, is a vast complex covering 12,000 square meters. It consists of themed exhibition halls showcasing ancient pottery, Buddhist art, and changing international exhibits. The museum's extensive collection includes historical and cultural artifacts such as ancient ceramics, bronze ware, and Shu brocade. With 14 meticulously curated exhibition halls, it offers visitors a glimpse into the region's rich heritage.
name: Sichuan Museum
address: 251 Huanhua S Rd, Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610032

excerpt: Showy Taoist palace with a large pavilion & artifacts, known for 2 black, bronze goat statues.
detail_description: Qingyang Palace, also known as Qingyang Monastery, is a grand Taoist shrine in Chengdu, China. It is one of the oldest and largest temples in the city, offering a serene escape from the urban bustle. The palace features notable structures such as Hunyuan Hall, Eight-Diagram Pavilion, Hall of Three Purities, and more. Visitors can admire artifacts and two striking black bronze goat statues.
name: Qingyang Palace （West Gate）
address: 9 1st Ring Rd West 2 Section, Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610032

detail_description: The Sichuan Opera Theater in Chengdu is a must-visit for an entertaining and culturally enriching experience. The theater, located in a historic building in central Chengdu, offers traditional Sichuanese Opera performances that are slightly different from regular Chinese opera. The shows feature various acts including face-changing, fire-breathing, acrobatics, hand shadowing, illusionists, and comedy.
name: Sichuan Opera Theater
address: 27 Hongzhaobi St, Luomashi, Jinjiang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610041

excerpt: Popular amusement park offering rollercoasters & other rides, a water park, dining & performances.
detail_description: Happy Valley Chengdu is a thrilling amusement park that offers a wide range of attractions for visitors of all ages. From exhilarating rollercoasters to water rides, this expansive park has something for everyone. In addition to the exciting rides, there are also numerous dining options and souvenir shops to explore. The park is known for its captivating performances, including acrobatics and extreme sports shows. With over 130 attractions, Happy Valley Chengdu promises an unforgettable experience filled with fun and adventure.
name: Happy Valley Chengdu
address: 16 Xihua Blvd, Jinniu District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610056

detail_description: Chengdu Yongling Museum, also known as the Eternal Mausoleum or Wang Jian's Tomb, is a well-preserved royal tomb located in the northwest section of Chengdu. The museum features a 15-meter-high building with 14 impressive archways and three chambers, one of which houses the exquisitely decorated sarcophagus of Emperor Wang Jian. Visitors can also enjoy close encounters with giant pandas, watch panda documentaries, and explore the surrounding areas for dining and shopping options.
name: Chengdu Yongling Museum
address: 10 Yongling Rd, Jinniu District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610031

detail_description: Heming Tea House is a popular spot in Chengdu, known for its diverse crowd and relaxed atmosphere. In this city, tea culture is unpretentious and focuses on creating an inviting environment for conversation and relaxation. Locals often spend hours here chatting or playing games like mahjong while enjoying sunflower seeds. This leisurely pace of life reflects the spirit of Chengdu, where slow living is highly valued.
name: Heming Tea House
address: M345+PCV, Citang St, 人民公园 Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610015

detail_description: Wide & Narrow Alley is a historical district in Chengdu, featuring architecture from the Ming and Qing dynasties. It consists of three parallel streets lined with private residences that have been renovated to accommodate restaurants, teahouses, and shops. Visitors can sample street food such as spicy tofu, fried seafood, meat skewers, and unconventional delicacies like duck heads. One popular snack is Long Chao Shou, a type of wonton stuffed with pork and vegetables served in a soup.
name: Wide & Narrow Alley
address: 双楠 Jin Jiang Qu, Cheng Du Shi, Si Chuan Sheng, China, 610093

excerpt: Sichuan is a southwestern Chinese province that contains a stretch of Asia’s longest river, the Yangtze. The region is the home of giant pandas, which visitors can observe at Bifengxia Panda Base and other reserves. Chengdu, the provincial capital, is a center for traditional Sichuanese opera, which include fire-breathing and sleight-of-hand mask changes.
detail_description: Sichuan, a province in southwestern China, is known for being the home of giant pandas. Visitors can observe these beloved creatures at places like Bifengxia Panda Base and other reserves. The provincial capital, Chengdu, is a vibrant city that boasts traditional Sichuanese opera and is famous for its spicy cuisine. It's also a place where ancient relics coexist with modern technologies, showcasing exceptional economic growth and future potential.
name: Sichuan
address: China

detail_description: Chengdu Huangcheng Mosque, located in the heart of the old Xicheng District, is a significant Muslim site in China with a rich history dating back to the 18th century. Despite being damaged during a Japanese air raid in 1941, it showcases a unique blend of traditional Chinese and Arabic architectural styles. The mosque's striking white walls adorned with colorful details and its expansive 16-meter-long prayer hall featuring original tiles are particularly noteworthy.
name: Chengdu Huangcheng Mosque
address: 2 Xiaohe St, Luomashi, Qingyang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610020

excerpt: The 20-hectare park & museum honoring Du Fu contains a replica of his cottage & copies of his works.
detail_description: Nestled in the western end of downtown Chengdu, China, Du Fu Thatched Cottage is a 20-hectare park and museum dedicated to honoring the great Tang Dynasty poet, Du Fu. The site features a replica of his cottage where he lived for four years and wrote around 240 poems. Surrounded by Huanhuaxi Park and Sichuan Museum, this historical gem has undergone extensive renovations and is now under national protection as a cultural heritage site.
name: 杜甫草堂
address: China, Sichuan, Chengdu, Qingyang District, Caotang Rd, 28号, 邮政编码: 610001

detail_description: Taikoo Li, also known as Sino-Ocean Taikoo Li, is a renowned fashion shopping and entertainment destination in Chengdu. It features over 300 stores, including big-label European designer brands like Cartier and Gucci. The venue's architecture combines Chinese-style elements with minimalist post-industrial design, creating a unique atmosphere. Visitors can explore high-end luxury goods as well as more affordable options.
name: Taikoo Li
address: 8 Zhongshamao St, Jinjiang District, Chengdu, Sichuan, China, 610000
